<paragraph id="8BF236B68775FFD3FF54F38032C1FD9A" blockId="1.[151,471,502,528]" box="[151,471,502,528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="503">
<heading id="D0BA81DA8775FFD3FF54F38032C1FD9A" bold="true" box="[151,471,502,528]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="503" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B939EAA48775FFD3FF54F38032C1FD9A" bold="true" box="[151,471,502,528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="503">
Subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D358775FFD3FEDCF38032C1FD9A" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[287,471,502,528]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ectrichodiinae">Ectrichodiinae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF236B68775FFD3FF54F04831BBFD62" blockId="1.[151,1437,574,745]" pageId="1" pageNumber="503">
There are 22 genera and more than 100 described species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D358775FFD3FC8EF04830E6FDD2" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[845,1008,574,600]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ectrichodiinae">Ectrichodiinae</taxonomicName>
in the New World (Gil-Santana 
<emphasis id="B939EAA48775FFD3FAA0F0493683FDD2" box="[1379,1429,574,600]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="503">et al</emphasis>
. 2015). Gil-Santana 
<emphasis id="B939EAA48775FFD3FEB7F01532B0FDF6" box="[372,422,610,636]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="503">et al</emphasis>
. (2015) provided a summary of the taxonomy of this group and a key to the genera of the New World. Because of the lack of consensus of previous authors about the validity or recognition of some genera (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B478775FFD3FF5CF0DC324FFD4E" author="Dougherty, V." box="[159,345,681,708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="503" pagination="173 - 225" refId="ref8601" refString="Dougherty, V. (1995) A review of the New World Ectrichodiinae genera (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 121, 173 - 225." type="journal article" year="1995">Dougherty 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B478775FFD3FEA0F0DC31A8FD4F" author="Carpintero, D. J. &amp; Maldonado, J." box="[355,702,682,709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="503" pagination="125 - 141" refId="ref8560" refString="Carpintero, D. J. &amp; Maldonado, J. (1996) Diagnostic characters and key to the genera of American Ectrichodiinae (Heteroptera, Reduviidae). Caribbean Journal of Science, 32, 125 - 141." type="journal article" year="1996">Carpintero &amp; Maldonado 1996</bibRefCitation>
), there is a need of a taxonomic revision and a phylogenetic analysis of all these genera (Gil-Santana 
<emphasis id="B939EAA48775FFD3FDE6F0B93140FD62" box="[549,598,718,744]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="503">et al</emphasis>
. 2015).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
